    "The details of trained NN are explained in Deep Neural Networks training section.H 1: y[n] = M i=1 x i [n; θ i] + M s i=1 x s,i [n; θ s,i] + η[n]The suggested approach operates on a per-satellite basis, with the input data for the NNs consisting of the associated CAF image for each satellite, which we denote with Z i ∈ R n τ ×n f in the sequel.It is possible to integrate this information into the hypothesis test, leading to the adaptation of a threshold γ.",
    "The details of calculating the test statistic can be found in [29].",
    "The test statistic that is derived as a result of this approach is such that The threshold γ serves as a tuning parameter for our spoofing detection algorithm.",
    "Since the test statistic is a ratio of probabilities, we have that 0 < T (Z i) < ∞.",
    "Similarly, as in [44], the DNNs provide estimated probabilities for each of the hypotheses in (10)."
  ]
}